description: This files contains test vectors for PKCS #8 encrypted keys.
The tests attempt to detect omissions and undefined behavior during decryption.
The validity of the test vector assumes that a key validation is performed.
Key derivation uses PBKDF2 with HMAC-SHA-512.
Encryption uses AES-CBC-192 with PKCS #7 padding.

references.title: Public-Key Cryptography Standards (PKCS) #8: Private-Key Information Syntax Specification Version 1.2

BerEncoding.desc: The ciphertext is BER encoded but not DER.

CVE-2025-0343.desc: The test vector contains a modification similar to the given CVE.

MismatchedKeySize.desc: The key size specified by the KDF parameters and the cipher algorithm are not the same.
MismatchedKeySize.effect: Implementations typically use the key size specified by the cipher algorithm.

MissingNull.desc: The ASN encoding of the Hmac algorithm contains an OID, but no NULL parameter

ModifiedPlaintext.desc: Fuzzing modified the plaintext. Key validation should fail

Pseudorandom.desc: The test vector has been generated pseudorandomly.

ShortSalt.desc: The salt size is smaller than 8 bytes
